1. Run this once:
amixer -c 0

2. Look for lines like:
Simple mixer control 'Speaker',0
Simple mixer control 'Headphone',0
Simple mixer control 'PCM',0

amixer -c 0 set Speaker 100% unmute

3. Create script:
nano ~/speaker-on-with-headphone.sh

4. paste this
#!/bin/bash

# Enable speaker even when headphone is plugged
amixer -c 0 set Speaker 100% unmute

# Ensure audio path is loud enough
amixer -c 0 set PCM 100% unmute
amixer -c 0 set Master 100% unmute

5. 
chmod +x ~/speaker-on-with-headphone.sh

6. 
nano ~/Desktop/Speaker+Headphone.desktop

7. 
[Desktop Entry]
Name=Enable Speaker with Headphone
Comment=Turn on speaker while headphone is connected
Exec=/home/abdul-mukit/speaker-on-with-headphone.sh
Icon=audio-speakers
Terminal=false
Type=Application
Categories=Audio;

8.
chmod +x ~/Desktop/Speaker+Headphone.desktop

9.
Right-click the .desktop file
Click “Allow Launching”

